financial issues –  bankruptcy and recovery   acquisition of arbinet –present  ptgi delists from nyse   ptgi renamed hc holdings inc   united kingdom operations  see also  references  external links historyedit beginnings –edit primus commenced operations in  intent on being a global facilities based service provider they entered the us market in  by assembling their core management team and beginning operations in  primus began its global expansion by acquiring australias fourth largest telecommunications service provider axicorp in the same year primus obtained a longdistance carrier license in the newly deregulated united kingdom and also released their initial public offering they completed their public listing the following year with the completion of the sale of more than us million in senior notes and warrants global expansion –edit primus global expansion continued in  with key acquisitions and international network expansion they completed the build and activation of their australian switched network international gateway switches in new york and los angeles and transpacific links  was also the beginning of primus growth through acquisitions in april primus purchased camnet communications network inc to allow them to enter the canadian long distance market later that year primus acquired telepassport llc and the assets of usfi inc this expanded primus long distance services operations into germany japan austria switzerland and south africa  saw primus expand their operations further in australia with the acquisition of eclipse telecommunications pty ltd and hotkey internet services pty limited these acquisitions along with primus new australian carriers license meant they were able to offer internet and data services to australians this however was not primus most significant activity in  in february that year they announced the acquisition of trescom international inc for a sum of us million which was later completed for us million the completion of this acquisition increased primus customer base to approximately  corporate small and mediumsized business residential and wholesale customers in the north america europe and the asiapacific regions that same year primus received international carrier status from canadas radio and telephone commission and signed a significant deal with qwest for fibre and increased bandwidth capacity for their us points of presence in march  primus canadian subsidiary purchased torontobased london telecom group inc earlier in the year primus also purchased globalserve communications a privately owned canadian internet service provider these acquisitions were closely followed by the purchase of many of the retail operations of telegroup inc including their australian subsidiary a longdistance telephone company based in fairfield iowa with  customers around the world telegroup was in chapter  bankruptcy before primus purchased their assets for  million primus growth did not end there in march the same year they were granted a type  telecommunications carrier license in japan which made them one of the first foreignbased carriers to be awarded the license they were also approved for a public telecommunications operations license to offer voice telephony services in france and to capitalise on their agreement to interconnect with deutsche telekom they purchased german internet service provider tcpip gmbh these developments and primus investment in paneuropean fibre optic systems such as their atlantic crossing  aphrodite aphrodite arianne cantat gemini and tat meant primus at the time offered services to  major cities located in  countries including austria denmark england france germany italy the netherlands norway spain sweden and switzerland primus continued to pursue growth through the purchase of assets in  they purchased a  controlling stake in brazils fifth largest internet service provider matrix internet sa to gain access to the brazilian market they also acquired dsl provider digitalselect llc to improve their residential broadband capabilities and firm  technologies to add ecommerce and web services capabilities to the organisation peak –edit the new millennium brought about success for primus with the global company being recognised by the technology industry in january primus won the washington technology fast  award later that year they were recognised by deloitte  touche as the fastest growing technology company according to their fast  ranking an award subsequently won by ebay in  and google in  primus continued their network expansion by furthering their relationship with qwest they signed an agreement to purchase capacity for their nationwide fiber optic cable ring and connecting routes this agreement came on the back of announcements that primus had begun strategic alliances with akamai technologies and hewlett packard their relationship with akamai involved an agreement to jointly deploy akamai servers in select primus points of presence to further akamais global content delivery capabilities primus venture with hewlett packard involved both parties joining forces to provide business services through hppowered data centres across primus global network the relationship involved a us million investment by hewlett packard while primus continued expanding their atm and ip networks in the us and internationally they also continued their acquisition growth strategy by purchasing lcr telecom group a londonbased voice and data reseller infinity online systems inc a canadian internet service provider a  stake in bekkoame internet inc a japanese internet service provider shorenet a newengland based internet service provider with data centre facilities and internext sa a french internet service provider with national operations these acquisitions also coincided with primus entering the puerto rico market by partnering with virtual inc and receiving a competitive local exchange carrier clec license at its peak in march  primus stock price was valued at us per share and the business was generating us billion in revenue annually us financial downturn –edit following the dotcom bubble bursting in  and the subsequent us financial downturn and stock market crash in  after september  primus reportedly began scaling back growth plans and reducing their debt in response to their stock value dropping to us in june  this preemptive measure allowed primus to avoid bankruptcy at the time and continue to remain profitable and record a full year earnings before interest taxes depreciation and amortization ebitda of  million in  primus did make some acquisitions in this period purchasing the us retail voice customer base of cable  wireless in  canadian internet provider magma communications ltd and in australia the internet service and interactive media businesses of aol as well as small australian dotcom firms useoz blue mountains internet and standardnet this period was still a period of growth and relative success for primus in  primus was added to the russell  index a us equity indexes that captures the  largest us stocks based on market capitalsation they were included in the  fortune  forbes magazines ranking of the largest public companies based on revenue in the united states and a  telegeography study found primus was on aggregate the worlds fifth largest carrier of international public switched telephone network pstn voice traffic primus also used this period of growth to move their stock from the nasdaq smallcap market to the nasdaq national market to gain more transparency financial issues –edit towards the end of  primus stock fell  and continued to fall in  as their core revenue streams of longdistance telephone service dialup internet connections and prepaid calling began shrinking to remedy this trend primus announced they would be shifting their focus from their long distance voice heritage to become a fully integrated service providercapable of delivering and bundling high growth telecommunication services including local wireless and broadbandwith the capability of offering arrays of bundled wirelinewirelessbroadbandvoip products in its major markets in  primus made their first product release inline with their new vision by releasing a highspeed voip internet phone service dubbed lingo designed to leverage primus international data network to provide a cost effective retail voice service lingo offered us customers unlimited calling in the us canada and western europe for only  per month despite  revenue growth in primus new services broadband and voip on march   primus telecommunications stock was transferred from the nasdaq national market to the nasdaq capital market due to the value of the stock dropping below  this setback however did not stop the business from continuing to roll out their own dslam network internationally especially in australia in  primus telecom admitted paying more than  million to settle a lawsuit alleging illegal or fraudulent transfers of funds primus telecom has also been named as a defendant in additional federal litigation as of  the companys stock had dropped more than  from its peak in early  amid declining revenue and accelerating losses according to the companys sec filings primus did not maintain effective internal control over financial reporting as of december   due to the material weakness in the company’s internal control over accounting for income taxes bankruptcy and recovery edit primus struggles finally culminated in the company filing for chapter  bankruptcy protection on march   months later however primus successfully emerged from chapter  on july   the value recovered by shareholders of old common stock ticker nasdaqprtl will depend on the companys financial performance over the four years following their emergence from chapter  as a result of the reorganisation primus creditors have also become significant share holders in the organisationcitation needed under the terms of the plan of reorganization primus has reduced its debt by  million or  and will emerge from bankruptcy with approximately  million of debt additionally primus reduced interest payments by approximately  and extended certain debt maturities none of primus operating companies in the united states australia canada india europe or brazil were included in the restructuring the operating units have and will continue to manage and to operate their businesses normally the newly emerged public company was not listed on any stock exchange until june   when it began trading under the ticker ptgi on the nyse acquisition of arbinet –presentedit as of march   primus appeared on the recovery track as they reported  net revenue of us million and free cash flow of  million revenue increases they claim are partly the result of sales of ippbx data hosting and other managed services to small and medium enterprises on  november  primus announced the acquisition of arbinet corporation a leading provider of international voice and ip solutions to carriers and service providers globally arbinet provides sophisticated platform intelligence call routing and industry leading credit management and settlement capabilities the deal was reportedly worth approximately  million in a stockforstock transaction reportedly arbinet shareholders will own approximately  of the combined company and primus shareholders are expected to own approximately  of the combined company with more than  carriers across the world utilizing the arbinet network primus expects the deal to add  million a year in revenue to its global wholesale group and deliver costs savings of  million to  million for each of the first two years ptgi delists from nyse edit on november   ptgis board of directors decided to delist from the nyse and deregister its common stock saying that the savings that would benefit shareholders and the company outweighed the advantages of continuing as a nyse listed and a reporting company without the annual accounting and legal costs and administrative burdens associated with sec reporting obligations and compliance with sarbenesoxley act ptgi said it would be able to reduce its costs while still maintaining an environment with appropriate financial controls ptgi renamed hc holdings inc edit on january   hrg group inc reported a  stake in ptgi on april   ptgi was renamed hc holdings inc united kingdom operationsedit primus had a subsidiary in the united kingdom a management buyout of the uk business in  saw this subsidiary separate from primus telecom to form new call telecom see alsoedit primus canada primus telecom australia broadband internet access australia referencesedit  a b investor relations hc   investor relations hc   investor relations hc   investor relations hc   structural steel fabrication and design  schuff steel schuffcom   global marine systems  subsea excellence since  globalmarinesystemscom   investor relations hc   a b c httpwwwprimustelcomimagesprimustimelineswf  primus telecommunications acquires axicorp australias fourth largest telecommunications service provider pr newswire march   retrieved    primus announces completion of portions of its network delays in migrating customers to its network and expected impact on revenue and gross margin pr newswire february   retrieved    primus telecommunications reports additional second quarter results q  revenue up  vs q  pr newswire august   retrieved    primus telecommunications acquires telepassport and assets of usfi primus expands into japan and germany pr newswire october   retrieved    primus acquires data communications service provider pr newswire april   retrieved    hotkey history hotkey retrieved    primus awarded full carrier license in australia  expects equal access to begin in july   pr newswire july   retrieved    primus to acquire trescom for  million pr newswire february   retrieved    company news primus agrees to buy a rival trescom for  million ny times february   retrieved    primus completes  million merger with tr